.TH CHECK\-HEALTH 1 "2026-04-04" "machine-setup 2.0" "Machine Setup Manual"
.SH NAME
check\-health.sh \- verify installed packages, dotfile symlinks, and service status
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B check\-health.sh
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Verifies that the current machine state matches the desired profile
configuration. Checks that all expected packages are installed, dotfile
symlinks are intact and point to the correct targets, and managed services
are running.
.PP
Outputs a summary of passed checks, warnings, and errors.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-profile " " \fINAME\fR
Profile to check against.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show the help message and exit.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
All checks passed; system is healthy.
.TP
.B 1
One or more warnings or errors were found.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Check health for the full profile:
.B check\-health.sh \-\-profile full
.TP
Check health for a custom profile:
.B check\-health.sh \-\-profile mysetup
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR setup.sh (1)
.SH AUTHORS
Machine Setup contributors.
